{
  "stem": "21786.9",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was in grave debt, so I decided after two years of residency to go into general practice so that I pay my debt back.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And meanwhile, I-- four years later-- got my mother into Canada, who came in and had a full stroke in the plane.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And she stayed in the hospital for an enormous quantity of time, and our finances were drained so I stayed in general practice.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I became very, very successful at that point.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And just out of curiosity, I wanted to continue to study.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So in 1965, after taking many courses, some of them together with Eva, I get the PhD in Literature from the Universite de Montreal.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I continued with my practice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In 1969, I had decided that it's the highest time I switched to something else.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I took training in psychoanalysis and additional training in psychiatric training.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And in 1975, I got qualified.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I started doing solely psychotherapy, with a certain exception for all my friends who came with me-- who went with me in the camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They did not recognize that I am doing psychiatry for them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I'm still simply a practitioner, which is quite good.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that's how I came to Canada.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just, [INAUDIBLE], probably.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Be prepared.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I believe simply that maybe humanity learned something, but in very small doses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, the cruelty of man to man has no end, and the kind of division between people is being kept artificially by so many means and ways.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That the-- they have to have their eyes and ears open and be well-trained and well-prepared.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I hope that they inherited some, maybe, of the intuitiveness I might have inherited from my forefathers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
